WEBVTT

00:00:00.160 --> 00:00:03.762
Lately, the Lord said, 'Brandon, I need you to encourage my people.

00:00:03.763 --> 00:00:17.125
I need you to tell them about what's coming: about the glory, about the last outpouring, the Holy Ghost, miracle restoration, and revival.'I'm excited to be with you all again today.

00:00:17.126 --> 00:00:26.938
I have another video for you, of course. I told you all it's like looking at a thin quarter or whatever you have in your country—a coin.

00:00:26.939 --> 00:00:31.929
You can either focus on the dark or you can focus on the light.

00:00:31.930 --> 00:00:44.711
It's like two sides of a coin: the darkness is going to get darker in these last days with the birthing pains, but the Lord told me the light is going to start getting lighter.

00:00:44.712 --> 00:00:53.059
You can see it; it'll be tangible. The last outpouring, a great harvest of souls, is what's about to happen.

00:00:53.060 --> 00:01:17.861
We're about to see one of the greatest things, like Bible times, like when Moses parted the Red Sea and walked across dry land, the plagues, and all the things you know—seeing blinded eyes open, deaf ears pop open, and autistic children completely delivered and set free by the power of God.

00:01:17.862 --> 00:01:27.000
We're about to see those things. If the Bible were still being written today, we would be part of the next chapter.

00:01:27.001 --> 00:01:33.041
I truly believe it with all my heart; that's how amazing these miracles are going to be.

00:01:33.043 --> 00:01:38.999
I believe with all my heart that people will be translating from one place to another, going and preaching the gospel.

00:01:39.000 --> 00:01:51.586
You may be in a city in America and all of a sudden you're in Africa, Asia, Australia, or South America.

00:01:51.587 --> 00:01:58.025
I believe those are the kinds of things we're going to start to see—the glory of God.

00:01:58.026 --> 00:02:19.945
These testimonies that I'm about to show you, that Sister Billye here—she read off a bunch of prophecies that Brother Hagin gave from the '80s and the '70s and right before he went home, about the last outpouring, about the glorious church rising up and being what we were called to be.

00:02:19.946 --> 00:02:31.361
This one was given in 1980: 'We're right on the verge of the greatest move and manifestation of the spirit of God this world has ever seen.

00:02:31.362 --> 00:02:53.334
Praise God, here we go.'And if you'll give the more earnest heed unto these things which you have heard—so think about, this was back in 1980 about faith and healing—but those things which you've heard about the Holy Spirit, about angels, about divine visitations, about visions and dreams.

00:02:53.335 --> 00:03:10.392
'And upon my handmaidens I'll pour out my spirit and they'll prophesy; my young men will prophesy, the young women will prophesy.'The anointing and the outflow of the spirit of God shall be great and amazing in these days, and there shall be visitations of angels.

00:03:10.393 --> 00:03:18.079
He goes on to speak about the glory of the Lord and the cloud of glory. Praise God!

00:03:18.080 --> 00:03:23.883
Gloria likes this part so much; it's one of her favorite prophecies from Brother Hagin.

00:03:23.884 --> 00:03:35.145
'You will flow in the supernatural as your mind will be changed.'Praise God! I renew mine now; I didn't catch that part before, Gloria.

00:03:35.146 --> 00:03:51.393
'Your heart shall be prepared and your mind will be changed until you will flow in the supernatural as naturally as a bird flies in the air.

00:03:51.394 --> 00:04:03.492
You will flow in the supernatural as naturally as a fish will swim in water.

00:04:03.493 --> 00:04:06.826
You will flow in the supernatural as naturally as you breathe the very air.'Praise God!

00:04:06.827 --> 00:04:16.677
'You will not be conscious of your faith; you'll not be conscious of what's going on around you, but rather you'll be more conscious of the flow of the spirit of God.

00:04:16.678 --> 00:04:21.588
He will manifest himself and he will accomplish that which he desires for you.

00:04:21.589 --> 00:04:27.353
See, these are the last days and this is the end time.'Thank you, Jesus!

00:04:27.354 --> 00:04:38.879
'And you shall walk, and you shall run, and you shall fly.'Praise God, literally and spiritually speaking!

00:04:38.880 --> 00:05:06.450
Hallelujah! I chose some other ones because I want you to see this one given in 2002. The Lord told us what to do to get it.

00:05:06.451 --> 00:05:17.935
'We are just about to enter into an area in the realm of the spirit in which only a few of us have touched, but it will be widespread.'Thank you, Jesus!

00:05:17.936 --> 00:05:26.992
'And all whose hearts are open, and whose minds are clear, and who are sincere and honest—those are the ones that will move in.

00:05:26.993 --> 00:05:34.422
For a great cloud of glory is hanging just over our heads.'Praise God!

00:05:34.423 --> 00:05:45.038
'And that cloud will burst into a torrent of outflow of the rain of the spirit.'That's what you saw, Lucy.

00:05:45.039 --> 00:05:57.762
'And the power of God shall not only be in us but rest upon us, and the plan and the purpose of God shall be consummated.'God has a plan!

00:05:57.763 --> 00:06:09.839
Not only for your life and mine, not only for your church and my ministry, but God has a plan for the last days. Be honest, sincere, and determined.

00:06:09.840 --> 00:06:23.834
'I'm walking and will walk in his plan and fulfill his purpose, for these are the last days.'It's time for us to change our thinking in some areas.

00:06:23.834 --> 00:06:31.740
It's time for us to listen to our hearts and listen to our spirits for counsel. 'I need counseling!

00:06:31.741 --> 00:06:38.339
Can you counsel me?'You have a counselor on the inside of you, the Holy Spirit, and he will counsel with you.

00:06:38.340 --> 00:06:45.388
He will talk to you; he will talk with you. He will instruct you; he will show you just what to do, and you'll be glad.

00:06:45.389 --> 00:06:49.758
And the plan of God will be consummated and the end shall come.

00:06:49.759 --> 00:07:02.077
The dead in Christ shall rise, and we which are alive and remain will be caught up together to meet the Lord in the air, and so shall we ever be with the Lord. So rejoice and be glad! Praise God!

00:07:02.078 --> 00:07:19.500
Now, this one: 'There will be a revival of the supernatural—not only the supernatural in casting out devils, not only the supernatural in healing the sick, not only the supernatural in speaking with other tongues, but the supernatural in the seen realm.

00:07:19.501 --> 00:07:36.719
Men will see the glory of God. A cloud will hang over certain congregations, even the church buildings, for days at a time.'And everybody who passes by—sinner and saint alike—will say, 'What in the world is that?

00:07:36.720 --> 00:07:46.195
I've never seen anything like that!'And there will be in other places the fire of the spirit that will actually become literal.

00:07:46.196 --> 00:07:54.995
In the spirit realm, some of us have seen it; we've been conscious of the fire of God, but the fire will actually come into manifestation.

00:07:54.996 --> 00:08:00.990
There will be people, sinners as well as saints, that will see fire over the heads of the people.

00:08:00.991 --> 00:08:20.796
There will be people driving down the street or down the highway and they'll see fire on the tops of the buildings, and they will come and say, 'What does all this mean?'But you see—now get this—the Lord will use signs of his presence to bring people in in the last days.

00:08:20.797 --> 00:08:27.401
That's how we're going to get the harvest right there. The outpouring of the spirit is going to draw them in.

00:08:27.402 --> 00:08:34.585
'I will use signs of his to bring people in in the last days.'Praise the Lord!

00:08:34.586 --> 00:08:43.022
Men and women too will be transported like Philip was and found in another place.

00:08:43.023 --> 00:08:51.063
And great shall be the reward thereof, for the Lord God is the same today as he was yesterday.

00:08:51.064 --> 00:08:54.814
His power has not diminished and his name is still the same today.

00:08:54.815 --> 00:09:05.086
He can make the iron ax head float today; he can divide the river just for two men to cross over today; he can feed five thousand with a little boy's lunch.

00:09:05.087 --> 00:09:11.799
He is the miracle-working God! Yes, this is what I've been looking for lately: the instruction.

00:09:11.800 --> 00:09:30.776
What do we do? Listen: 'Brag on him.'Praise the Lord! Brag on him, lift him up, draw attention unto him, tell about how great he is.

00:09:30.777 --> 00:09:40.697
How awesome is our God! Lord, do that tonight: get up in faith and tell what great things he's going to do.

00:09:40.698 --> 00:09:51.084
He's going to do it, and we're going to see it! Hallelujah! 'For the purpose of it all is that you may be fishers of men.

00:09:51.085 --> 00:09:58.805
Quit fishing in your own bathtubs; there are not any fish in your own bathtub!

00:09:58.806 --> 00:10:06.554
Go out where the fish are and throw out the nets—not the hook, the nets—and pull them in!'Hallelujah!

00:10:06.555 --> 00:10:16.702
And bring them in, and the glory of the Lord shall shine, and the end time shall come, and he's going in the Holy Ghost.

00:10:16.702 --> 00:10:30.100
He's been praying in the Holy Ghost, and he begins to say this: 'Moving into that place is fueled by prayer.

00:10:30.101 --> 00:10:39.007
It's fueled by prayer, fired by the Spirit, and ignited with His glory.'Wow, say that again.

00:10:39.008 --> 00:10:46.165
He got so tickled over saying that he started saying, 'Hallelujah to Jesus, glory to God.'I said, 'Glory to God, glory to God, hallelujah.'Fueled by prayer.

00:10:46.166 --> 00:11:07.518
And he starts talking about it; he said, 'If there's no fuel, there's nothing to ignite.'He said, 'Notice what the Spirit said.'I never thought of it—it came out of the inside of me—he said, 'I never thought of it before: fueled by prayer, fired by the Spirit, and ignited with His glory.'We have to stop and analyze that.

00:11:07.519 --> 00:11:14.526
Then he comes to this: 'If there is no fuel, there's nothing to fire.

00:11:14.527 --> 00:11:30.758
If there's no fuel, there's nothing to fire. It is fueled by prayer.'We've got a big key here: prayer.

00:11:30.759 --> 00:11:40.837
All this praying in the Spirit, the Holy Ghost said, is going to be fueled by prayer.

00:11:40.838 --> 00:11:52.900
There will be churches in the body of Christ, in buildings where they meet, where the glory of God will fill the place like a cloud and everybody will see it.

00:11:52.901 --> 00:12:04.708
And when that glory comes in manifestation, people walking by and driving by in their cars, even the unsaved, will feel the power; and folks down at the end of the block will fall under the power in their homes.

00:12:04.709 --> 00:12:25.221
Thank You, Father. And they will wonder, 'What is this strange power that's in manifestation for the glory of God?'And the power of God will, like a cloud, hang over whole cities because you prayed—because you believed.

00:12:25.222 --> 00:12:42.783
I just want to do a recap here. So, here we are. She's talking about how we're going to fuel this end-time revival, how we get the manifestation of what we're believing for instead of just waiting for it to happen.

00:12:42.784 --> 00:12:56.132
I know it's in God's timing, but just like Brother Hagin was talking about it, prayer is a major key to this, interceding for the last outpouring.

00:12:56.133 --> 00:13:18.716
Just like it was—you know, if we go back to what John Kilpatrick said with the Pensacola Revival—they had prayer there every night for a while, and they prayed for two years for a revival to break out in that area.

00:13:18.717 --> 00:13:28.039
And so it was birthed through intercessory prayer, continually praying in the Spirit.

00:13:28.040 --> 00:13:43.560
That church prayed and prayed, and then on a Father's Day, the manifestation of the outpouring started to manifest and took place. It came.

00:13:43.561 --> 00:13:58.418
At its very start, there were three men: George Whitefield, John Wesley, and Charles Wesley—three Englishmen—and they formed a club called The Holy Club.

00:13:58.419 --> 00:14:06.833
In their Holy Club, they endeavored to live a holy life and to pray.

00:14:06.834 --> 00:14:16.078
Their Holy Club had an unusual thing that happened to it. I shall read you about it right here.

00:14:16.079 --> 00:14:28.174
I wonder what book that is. It had grown to 32 members when there came—just think about that right there.

00:14:28.175 --> 00:14:32.879
Sorry to interrupt again, but 32 people praying, that's all.

00:14:32.880 --> 00:14:42.975
Whenever I do a prayer thing on here, we'll have 3,500 people pray in the Spirit for at least 15 minutes.

00:14:42.976 --> 00:14:51.145
So just think about that; we have great power and unity in prayer. So, thirty-some people here.

00:14:51.146 --> 00:14:57.733
Upon them, a great outpouring of the Spirit on New Year's Day, 1739.

00:14:57.734 --> 00:15:06.691
Over 60 people were present at that moment when the Wesleys, George Whitefield, and others received God's power in the Spirit.

00:15:06.692 --> 00:15:14.180
Waves of unspeakable joy passed over them, and they prostrated themselves on the ground in awe and adoration.

00:15:14.181 --> 00:15:20.124
Thank God. It gave these men a deep conviction that He was about to do something great and wonderful in England.

00:15:20.125 --> 00:15:30.598
And as this great revival moved, it brought them to America. It moved in the English-speaking world.

00:15:30.599 --> 00:15:38.298
There are chapters in here—Paul Brady, where are you?—about how it moved to Ulster and how it moved to Belfast and the things that happened.

00:15:38.299 --> 00:15:53.724
But in the United States of America, it became known as the Great Awakening. It was from 1739 until 1791.

00:15:53.725 --> 00:16:02.429
There was a great connection between the Great Awakening and the American Revolution.

00:16:02.430 --> 00:16:14.498
The outcome of the Great Awakening was the United States of America.

00:16:14.499 --> 00:16:25.636
And one of the leaders—and these things are all in this book right here—was greatly affected by a man named Finney.

00:16:25.637 --> 00:16:46.893
The Finney revivals. And there's so much clue in here as to what happened with Finney, and I want to read you just a little bit of it. Bless the Lord, hallelujah. Revival fires follow Finney.

00:16:46.894 --> 00:16:58.758
His biographer said that perhaps the most remarkable account of the manifestations of the Holy Spirit's power since apostolic days was in Finney's meetings.

00:16:58.759 --> 00:17:03.809
It is crowded with accounts of spiritual outpourings which remind one of the Day of Pentecost.

00:17:03.810 --> 00:17:12.119
The intensity and constancy of his ardor were surprising. The sacred fire never seemed to burn low.

00:17:12.120 --> 00:17:25.036
His campaign, which began in New York State, was absolutely preparing the way for the mighty move of revival that swept America in 1857 and 1858.

00:17:25.037 --> 00:17:37.177
More than a million people came into the kingdom of God under his ministry, and though the population was not so large, 85% of the professed converts in the Finney revivals remained true to God.

00:17:37.178 --> 00:17:44.039
These revivals spread and blessed churches from city to city and around and across America.

00:17:44.040 --> 00:17:59.970
God poured—in the early days of his walk with the Lord, Finney learned about prevailing prayer and prayer burdens, and he would spend time in prayer, often going to the woods to be alone with God.

00:17:59.971 --> 00:18:06.634
God poured out a spirit of prayer upon other people who followed Finney and went with him.

00:18:06.635 --> 00:18:14.977
Much private prayer accompanied this revival. And so Finney began to preach. He went to a town in New York named Antwerp.

00:18:14.978 --> 00:18:21.147
He walked through the streets, he heard profanity, and he spent the rest of the day in prayer.

00:18:21.148 --> 00:18:27.925
And before a few days, most of its 2,250 citizens were converted.

00:18:27.926 --> 00:18:33.476
Wow. He visited a nearby village. In the first service, the schoolhouse was full.

00:18:33.477 --> 00:18:40.302
After 15 minutes, the congregation began to fall from their seats. They fell in every direction and cried for mercy.

00:18:40.303 --> 00:18:46.271
'If I had had a sword in each hand, I could not have cut them all from their seats as fast as they fell,'he wrote.

00:18:46.272 --> 00:18:50.473
Indeed, nearly the whole congregation were either on their knees or prostrate.

00:18:50.474 --> 00:18:58.206
'I think in less than two minutes from the first shock that fell upon them, everyone prayed for himself who was able to pray at all.

00:18:58.207 --> 00:19:06.693
I, of course, was obliged to stop preaching, for no one any longer paid attention to me.'Do it again, do it again, Lord.

00:19:06.694 --> 00:19:11.214
The meetings went on and on, and whole towns would get saved.

00:19:11.215 --> 00:19:16.869
He went to New York, Oneida County. God gave a prayer burden on Friday.

00:19:16.870 --> 00:19:24.638
Sunday, God came in power at the church services. Finney prevailed in prayer and spoke in several parts of the town.

00:19:24.639 --> 00:19:33.352
A Mrs. Harris had wrestled in prayer night and day. When she met Finney, she said, 'The Lord has come. This work will spread over all this region.

00:19:33.353 --> 00:19:40.900
A cloud of mercy overhangs us, and we shall see a great work of grace that has never yet been seen.'Finney said that Mrs.

00:19:40.901 --> 00:19:45.402
Harris's face had a most unearthly, heavenly glow that was plainly from Heaven.

00:19:45.403 --> 00:19:49.557
She had won a revival through prayer. Praise God, through prayer.

00:19:49.558 --> 00:19:54.196
And then after the revival fire burned in the West for a while, it came to the town of Rome.

00:19:54.197 --> 00:20:00.007
God gripped the people with such Holy Spirit conviction, Finney was afraid that the people could not control their emotions.

00:20:00.008 --> 00:20:08.217
Finney led in prayer at the close of the meeting in a low, unemotional voice, trying to restrain the people who had begun to weep and sigh.

00:20:08.218 --> 00:20:12.944
He urged them to control their feelings and go home without speaking a word to anyone.

00:20:12.945 --> 00:20:18.335
The people obeyed, but their sighing and sobbing continued as they went down the street to their homes.

00:20:18.336 --> 00:20:25.839
At daybreak, the people began sending for Finney. He spent the morning going from house to house to pray with the people.

00:20:25.840 --> 00:20:32.357
He finally announced a meeting for inquirers, and many more were convicted in the evening service.

00:20:32.358 --> 00:20:38.905
People were so overwhelmed by the Holy Spirit's conviction that he dismissed the service and asked the people to go home.

00:20:38.906 --> 00:20:45.794
Revival went on for twenty nights with a prayer meeting once a day, a meeting for inquirers at another time, and ministers'meetings at night.

00:20:45.795 --> 00:20:50.867
Some people collapsed from conviction in the church services and some later in their own homes.

00:20:50.868 --> 00:20:58.945
It had become common across America that people, by and large, in great groups of cities, were not born again.

00:20:58.946 --> 00:21:02.172
He would go into these places and these things would happen.

00:21:02.173 --> 00:21:09.918
Three men spent a day drinking and condemning the revival until one of them fell down dead.

00:21:09.919 --> 00:21:16.443
Nearly all of the adult population of Rome, New York, was brought to Christ—lawyers, merchants, physicians, and town leaders.

00:21:16.444 --> 00:21:26.356
The ministers said, "So far as my congregation is concerned, the Millennium has come."Everyone who came into the village felt an overwhelming sense of God's presence.

00:21:26.357 --> 00:21:33.952
The sheriff of Utica, New York, twenty miles away, came on business. He had laughed and mocked at the reports of the revival.

00:21:33.953 --> 00:21:41.298
As his sleigh crossed the canal one mile outside of Rome, an awesome feeling of the presence of God gripped him.

00:21:41.299 --> 00:21:45.632
The nearer to the village he came, the more powerfully he sensed God's presence.

00:21:45.633 --> 00:21:55.769
The sheriff found the people in the business establishments too overcome with the awe of God—so overcome they could hardly speak without trying to keep from weeping.

00:21:55.770 --> 00:22:02.607
The sheriff got up several times and went to the window. He hurried to complete his business and hastened back to Utica.

00:22:02.608 --> 00:22:09.213
Soon he was converted. Bless the Lord, Finney urged the people to pray to God earnestly.

00:22:09.214 --> 00:22:25.278
Now get this; here's one part I want to highlight: Finney would go into a town and he would urge the people to pray to God earnestly and expectantly for the immediate outpouring of His Holy Spirit.

00:22:25.279 --> 00:22:32.526
He told them that if they united in prayer, they could get God's answer quicker than a letter could come from Albany, the state's capital.

00:22:32.527 --> 00:22:38.241
Several men agreed to prove God in that way and their prayer was answered just that quickly.

00:22:38.242 --> 00:22:45.319
Finney wrote, "Indeed, the town was full of prayer. Go where you would, you heard the voice of prayer.

00:22:45.320 --> 00:22:51.030
Pass along the streets, if two or three Christians happened to be together, they were praying. Wherever they met, they prayed.

00:22:51.031 --> 00:23:03.107
Wherever there was a sinner unconverted, especially if he manifested any opposition, you'd find two or three brothers or sisters agreeing to make him a particular subject of prayer."Hallelujah!

00:23:03.108 --> 00:23:12.168
That's what we have to do. The sheriff of Utica, a new convert, went back to the boarding house where he boarded and began to pray for the hotel keeper.

00:23:12.169 --> 00:23:22.345
In Utica, the Holy Ghost fell. A divine influence seemed to pervade Utica and Rome during these revivals and turned the area into a zone of holiness.

00:23:22.346 --> 00:23:28.015
The same phenomenon was occurring along the whole eastern coast of the United States.

00:23:28.016 --> 00:23:38.886
During the 1858 revival—which was a later one—the Oneida Presbytery met in Utica.

00:23:38.887 --> 00:23:45.769
An aged clergyman complained that everywhere he went in the town, people talked about prayer and revival.

00:23:45.770 --> 00:23:50.404
He got up in the presbytery meeting and made a violent speech against the revival.

00:23:50.405 --> 00:23:56.086
That night, many Christians prayed fervently that the revival would not be hindered by his speech.

00:23:56.087 --> 00:24:05.351
In the morning, this minister was found dead in his bed in the hotel.

00:24:05.351 --> 00:24:21.744
I've heard Brother Hagin prophesy that when this starts, there are going to be some people that are going to go on home, and he prophesied that there would be such judgments.

00:24:21.745 --> 00:24:31.587
I love this part about it: a Methodist church was formed in the town and then a Presbyterian church.

00:24:31.588 --> 00:24:40.043
When Finney would go to a town, he'd preach in one church, it would build; he'd go to another denomination, it would build.

00:24:40.044 --> 00:24:53.599
In the same towns, there would be different denominational churches and the whole town would have the revival and everybody's church would grow. I'll end that there, but I want to talk to you all about it.

00:24:53.600 --> 00:25:09.077
Whenever the Lord showed me about the time of revival—and I've told you whenever I've seen into it—the Lord showed me that the denominational barriers were coming down.

00:25:09.078 --> 00:25:19.342
I believe that, just like we have so much separation between the Baptists, the Methodists, the Catholics, the Presbyterians, and the Church of Christ, the Lord showed me.

00:25:19.343 --> 00:25:23.701
He said, "Brandon, for what's coming, it's going to be one body.

00:25:23.702 --> 00:25:41.373
All the different tents and all the different thinkings are going to come down through this great shaking that's about to take place."It's a great shaking, and so all of the body of Christ will come together as one.

00:25:41.374 --> 00:25:54.715
The Lord showed me this would be a massive molding of people because of a kind of camaraderie—kind of like when I told you all about 9/11.

00:25:54.716 --> 00:26:01.546
What happened at 9/11? There was a real camaraderie, a patriotism that happened over America.

00:26:01.547 --> 00:26:13.366
I believe there will be a patriotism in the body of Christ, a camaraderie where everybody's excited to work together for this last outpouring.

00:26:13.367 --> 00:26:31.622
I believe that we will see denominational barriers start to come down, and we're going to see this massive move of a wave of the Spirit of God upon all flesh, of a great harvest of souls.

00:26:31.623 --> 00:26:36.973
So I want to encourage you all listening to these old prophecies.

00:26:36.974 --> 00:26:42.394
Listen to these men of God and how they got it: they got it through prayer.

00:26:42.395 --> 00:26:57.275
How many stories were told and prophetic words were given about prayer, like I talked about John Kilpatrick and Finney and these people—they birthed it out of prayer.

00:26:57.276 --> 00:27:05.759
Even with the Azusa Street Revival, it happened out of a birthing out of prayer. That was in the 1900s.

00:27:05.760 --> 00:27:14.398
Here we are a hundred years later and we're about to see another revival, and I believe it will be birthed out of prayer.

00:27:14.399 --> 00:27:21.407
If it happened every single time before, it's going to happen again. So we're going to start praying more.

00:27:21.408 --> 00:27:38.882
We're going to pray for the revival, we're going to pray for an outpouring, we're going to pray for a harvest of souls—that people would wake up out of their compromise, wake up out of their spiritual slumber, their lukewarmness.

